In this article, President Barack Obama reports that he has issued an Executive Order to block the property and suspend entry into the United States of certain individuals involved in grave human rights abuses by the governments of Iran and Syria through information technology. The order aims to prevent entities in Iran and Syria from facilitating or committing serious human rights abuses. It also blocks the property and interests in property of those involved in operating information and communications technology that enables rights abuses, selling or providing goods or services likely to be used for rights abuses, providing support to those involved in such activities, or acting on behalf of blocked individuals. The Secretary of the Treasury has been delegated the authority to take necessary actions to carry out the order. All US government agencies are directed to implement the provisions of the order.